svg.text: Manhattan is the borough with the highest number of zipcodes in the highest quintile
of dog licenses (656 - 2380 dogs). Brooklyn follows Manhattan as the borough with
the second highest number of dog licenses. Queens has the lowest number of zipcodes
in the highest quintile of dog licenses. Interestingly, people who live in Queens' zipcodes
closer to Long Island and with bigger yards hold the least dog licenses. The number
of dog licenses in Staten Island and the Bronx are in between Brooklyn and Queens.

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font: bold 22px Arial; cursor: pointer; opacity: 1; display: none;
